                            <comment id="18948" author="costin" created="Tue, 8 Aug 2006 01:05:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll talk with Juergen and see if the solution proposed for hibernate at least, could make it inside an official release or not (maybe just some documentation). Once I&apos;ll return home, I&apos;ll take a look at the issues and start solving them (hopefully).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19081" author="costin" created="Wed, 16 Aug 2006 21:18:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve committed a simple implementation into the CVS - it uses a newly added ScopedObject method which returns the target object (which avoid being coupled to the underlying proxying mechanism).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19082" author="costin" created="Wed, 16 Aug 2006 21:19:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the record, the class is ScopedBeanInterceptor under org.sf.orm.hb3.support package.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
